# i18n Protocol (German & English)

## Rule

- NEVER use hardcoded strings in UI components.
- ALWAYS use `next-intl` (`useTranslations` hook) for any user-facing text.
- All keys must exist in both `frontend/messages/en.json` and `frontend/messages/de.json`.
- The i18n config lives at `frontend/i18n/request.ts` (non-routing setup with cookie-based locale).

## Workflow

- When creating a new feature, first define the labels in the JSON translation files.
- Use semantic, namespaced keys (e.g., `dashboard.stats.totalJobs`) rather than generic ones.
- Import `useTranslations` from `next-intl` and scope it to the relevant namespace.
- For interpolation, use ICU message format: `t("key", { variable: value })`.
